<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="layout" content="main">
  <title>Exit Survey</title>
  <link href="http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:400,400,600" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
  <asset:stylesheet src="standardize.css"/>
  <asset:stylesheet src="exitsurvey-grid.css"/>
  <asset:stylesheet src="exitsurvey.css"/>
</head>
<body class="body index clearfix">
  <div id="page1" class="page1 clearfix">
    <div class="text pleaseanswer text-1">
      <p>Please answer the following questions as honestly as you can. There are no right or wrong answers.&nbsp;<br>Your answers within this survey will not affect your ability to withdraw your funds.</p>
      <p>Thank you in advance for your participation!<br></p>
</div>
    <p class="text youwillbewithdr">You will be withdrawing from 3 TripleBoost account(s), whose names are: Apple, Bee, Cat</p>
    <p class="text q1">1. How old are Apple, Bee, and Cat?</p>
    <div class="agebox clearfix">
      <p class="text childnamelabel">Apple :&nbsp;      </p>
      <select class="ageinput" name="child_age">
        <option value="----">----</option>
        <option value="10">10</option>
        <option value="11">11</option>
        <option value="12">12</option>
        <option value="13">13</option>
        <option value="14">14</option>
        <option value="15">15</option>
        <option value="16">16</option>
        <option value="17">17</option>
        <option value="18">18</option>
        <option value="19">19</option>
        <option value="20">20</option>
        <option value="21">21</option>
      </select>
      <p class="text yearsold">years old      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="text q2">2. How often do you talk to Apple, Bee, and Cat about money?<br>Please include casual conversations such as talking about spending, saving, and what the family can afford.</p>
    <div class="q2lilbox clearfix">
      <p class="text childnamelabel">Apple &nbsp;:</p>
      <select class="freqmoney" name="frequency_talk_about_money">
        <option value="Select answer">Select answer</option>
        <option value="Almost every day.">Almost every day.</option>
        <option value="At least once a week.">At least once a week.</option>
        <option value="At least once a month.">At least once a month.</option>
        <option value="A few times a year.">A few times a year.</option>
        <option value="Never.">Never.</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    <p class="text q3">3. In the last week, how much time did you spend talking with Apple, Bee, and Test about their education?<br>Please include time spent talking about their classes, their teachers, what they're learning, or their extra-curricular activities.</p>
    <div class="q3lilbox clearfix">
      <p class="text childnamelabel">Apple &nbsp;:</p>
      <select class="freqeducation" name="frequency_talk_about_education">
        <option value="Select answer">Select answer</option>
        <option value="Less than an hour">Less than an hour</option>
        <option value="1 or 2 hours">1 or 2 hours</option>
        <option value="3 or more hours">3 or more hours</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    <p class="text q4">4. What do you expect from Apple, Bee, and Test in terms of education?<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; I expect my child to...</p>
    <div class="q4lilbox clearfix">
      <p class="text childnamelabel">Apple &nbsp;:</p>
      <select class="expectations" name="child_educational_expectations">
        <option value="Select answer">Select answer</option>
        <option value="Leave high school prior to graduation with a GED.">Leave high school prior to graduation with a GED.</option>
        <option value="Graduate from high school or get a GED.">Graduate from high school or get a GED.</option>
        <option value="Attend some college.">Attend some college.</option>
        <option value="Graudate from a vocational or trade school.">Graudate from a vocational or trade school.</option>
        <option value="Graduate from a 2-year or 4-year college.">Graduate from a 2-year or 4-year college.</option>
        <option value="Attend graduate school (Master's Degree, PhD, JD, MD, etc.).">Attend graduate school (Master's Degree, PhD, JD, MD, etc.).</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    <p class="text q5">5. What were the children's most recent grades in math?</p>
    <div class="q5lilbox clearfix">
      <p class="text childnamelabel">Apple &nbsp;:</p>
      <select class="grades" name="child_grades_math">
        <option value="Select answer">Select answer</option>
        <option value="A+, A, or A-">A+, A, or A-</option>
        <option value="B+, B, or B-">B+, B, or B-</option>
        <option value="C+, C, or C-">C+, C, or C-</option>
        <option value="D+, D, or D-">D+, D, or D-</option>
        <option value="F">F</option>
        <option value="My child's school does not have grades.">My child's school does not have grades.</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    <p class="text q6">6. What were the children's most recent grades in reading/writing?</p>
    <div class="q6lilbox clearfix">
      <p class="text childnamelabel">Apple &nbsp;:</p>
      <select class="grades" name="child_grades_reading_writing">
        <option value="Select answer">Select answer</option>
        <option value="A+, A, or A-">A+, A, or A-</option>
        <option value="B+, B, or B-">B+, B, or B-</option>
        <option value="C+, C, or C-">C+, C, or C-</option>
        <option value="D+, D, or D-">D+, D, or D-</option>
        <option value="F">F</option>
        <option value="My child's school does not have grades.">My child's school does not have grades.</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    <p class="text q7">7. Did Apple, Bee, and Test know you were saving for them in this account?</p>
    <div class="q7lilbox clearfix">
      <p class="text childnamelabel">Apple &nbsp;:</p>
      <select class="accountknowledge" name="child_account_knowledge">
        <option value="Select answer">Select answer</option>
        <option value="Yes">Yes</option>
        <option value="No">No</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    <button class="next">
      <p>Next</p>
      <p></p>
    </button>
  </div>
</body>
</html>